Berrya cordifolia

   Authority (Willd.) Burret
   Family Magnoliopsida:Dilleniidae:Malvales:Tiliaceae
   Synonyms Berrya ammonilla Roxb., Espera cordifolia Willd.,
   Hexagonotheca cordata Turcz., Triopteris polyandra Blanco
   Common names
   Editor
   Ecocrop code 3698

   Notes
   SOURCES (B. cordifolia (Willd.) Burret.)
   Joshi H 1980a pp 73-75 [TEMP, RAIN, DRA, TEXT, PH, LIG, USE]
   GROWING PERIOD
   Perennial deciduous tree. In India new leaves appears with the
   commencement of rains and are shed before the hot season. Flowers
   appear in July-August and the capsules ripen from December to March.
   COMMON NAMES
   Trincomalee wood, Tiriconamalai maram, Saraladevadaru
   FURTHER INF
   Scientific synonyms: B. ammonilla, B. mollis. Trincomalee wood can
   reach a height of 18-27 m. The tree is adapted to low land conditions.

   Sources

   FAO - Food and Agriculture Organization of the UN - Helping to build a
   world without hunger
